FT  16 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Reliance Security shares dip
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SHARES OF Reliance Security Group fell 18p to 123p following the
announcement of an 11 per cent downturn in pre-tax profits to Pounds 905,000
for the 27 weeks to November 6.
Mr Brian Kingham, chairman of the USM-quoted security provider, said the
fall included a reduced loss of Pounds 502,000 (Pounds 772,000) from the
electronic security surveillance business.
He was encouraged by an 8 per cent improvement in turnover to Pounds 34.1m
but pointed out that lower profits reflected the impact of recession which
was most notable in reduced margins.
Earnings amounted to 2.7p (3p) per share and the interim dividend is held at
1.1p.
