<HEADLINE>
FT  15 DEC 92 / Construction Contracts: Supplying equipment to power
stations
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NEI INTERNATIONAL COMBUSTION has won orders for power station combustion
equipment worth Pounds 25m in the UK and US.
In Britain, the company has won an order worth Pounds 18m to provide the
waste heat recovery steam generators for National Power at the company's
gas-fired combined cycle power station at Deeside.
In the US, the group has signed a further contract for the supply of
combustion equipment to Georgia Power. The contract is part of a four unit
order worth more than Pounds 7m.
The Deeside commission was placed by NEI ABB Gas Turbines, which won the
order to construct the 500MW plant last year.
