<HEADLINE>
FT  15 DEC 92 / International Company News: Accounts change leads Boeing to
take Dollars 1bn charge
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SEATTLE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BOEING, the US aerospace group, said it would implement the new Financial
Accounting Standards Board's Statement of Financial Accounting Standards 106
in 1992, resulting in a one-time, after-tax charge to earnings of Dollars
1bn, or Dollars 2.94 a share, AP-DJ reports from Seattle.
The company said the change would be reflected in restated first-quarter
results. In its 1991 annual report Boeing estimated an after-tax earnings
impact of between Dollars 900m and Dollars 1.2bn. For 1992, this will
represent a decrease in earnings per share of about 6 cents each quarter, it
added.
</TEXT>
