</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW DELHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
INDIAN police yesterday arrested scores of Hindu nationalists as they
marched towards the Pakistan High Commission in a demonstration organised by
the right-wing Hindu Bharatiya Janata party, the main opposition party,
whose supporters last week sacked a mosque and prompted a nationwide wave of
violence, writes Stefan Wagstyl in New Delhi.
