FT  15 DEC 92 / Construction Contracts: Pounds 7m orders won by Willmott
Dixon
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WILLMOTT DIXON SYMES' order book has been given a boost with awards of
Pounds 7m worth of building work in London.
In Covent Garden Willmott Dixon Symes is working on the refurbishment of two
adjoining Victorian buildings at the junction of Maiden Lane and Southampton
Street.
The Pounds 1.2m contract, for National Provident Institution, involves
knocking the two buildings into one, carrying out a total internal refit and
considerable structural work on the exterior of the buildings to restore
their period brick facades.
A similar contract, worth Pounds 867,000, is under way in Hammersmith, where
a Georgian building is being converted into a Deals restaurant as part of
the Bredero Centre West development.
