FT  15 DEC 92 / International Capital Markets: KPMG global fee income rises
2.3% over year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
KPMG PEAT MARWICK, the worldwide accounting network, reported global fee
income up 2.3 per cent to Dollars 6.15bn for the year to September 30,
writes Andrew Jack.
Audit fees grew 5 per cent to Dollars 3.2bn and tax advice by 7 per cent to
Dollars 1.3bn. The recession affected growth in Australia and New Zealand,
and also North America, where income fell 0.8 per cent to Dollars 2.23bn.
In common with other firms, KPMG does not provide any details of its profits
or assets.
It reported strong growth in eastern Europe, other parts of Asia Pacific and
Latin America, where income was up 14 per cent. The firm had 6,004 partners
and some 73,000 staff in 124 countries worldwide.
